James Version</TITLE><link rel=stylesheet href=style1.css type=text/css></HEAD> 
<BODY BACKGROUND='Image1.jpg'><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Sacred Name King James           
Version</H3><P><A HREF='B56C003.htm'>Titus 3</A></P><CENTER><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>   
The Epistle of Paul to Philemon</H2></CENTER><P><A HREF='index.htm'>Return to   
Index</A>.</P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD> 
<CENTER><H1>Chapter 1</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4> 
1</H4></TD><TD><P>Paul, a prisoner of YAHSHUA MASHIYACH, and Timothy our        
brother, unto Philemon our dearly beloved, and fellowlabourer,</P></TD></TR><TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>And to our beloved Apphia, and  
Archippus our fellowsoldier, and to the church in thy house:</P></TD></TR><TR>  
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>Grace to you, and peace, from   
ELOHIYM our Father and the ADONAY YAHSHUA MASHIYACH.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD       
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>I thank my ELOHIYM, making mention  
of thee always in my prayers,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>   
5</H4></TD><TD><P>Hearing of thy love and faith, which thou hast toward the     
ADONAY YAHSHUA, and toward all saints;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>That the communication of thy faith may become    
effectual by the acknowledging of every good thing which is in you in MASHIYACH 
YAHSHUA.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>For   
we have great joy and consolation in thy love, because the bowels of the saints 
are refreshed by thee, brother.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4> 
8</H4></TD><TD><P>Wherefore, though I might be much bold in MASHIYACH to enjoin 
thee that which is convenient,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>  
9</H4></TD><TD><P>Yet for love's sake I rather beseech thee, being such an one  
as Paul the aged, and now also a prisoner of YAHSHUA MASHIYACH.</P></TD></TR>   
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>I beseech thee for my son 
Onesimus, whom I have begotten in my bonds:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A  
NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>Which in time past was to thee unprofitable,    
but now profitable to thee and to me:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A        
NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>Whom I have sent again: thou therefore receive  
him, that is, mine own bowels:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4> 
13</H4></TD><TD><P>Whom I would have retained with me, that in thy stead he     
might have ministered unto me in the bonds of the gospel:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD  
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>But without thy mind would I do   
nothing; that thy benefit should not be as it were of necessity, but            
willingly.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>  
For perhaps he therefore departed for a season, that thou shouldest receive him 
for ever;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>   
Not now as a servant, but above a servant, a brother beloved, specially to me,  
but how much more unto thee, both in the flesh, and in the ADONAY?</P></TD></TR>
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P>If thou count me          
therefore a partner, receive him as myself.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A  
NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>If he hath wronged thee, or oweth thee ought,   
put that on mine account;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V19><H4>      
19</H4></TD><TD><P>I Paul have written it with mine own hand, I will repay it:  
albeit I do not say to thee how thou owest unto me even thine own self          
besides.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>20</H4></TD><TD><P>    
Yea, brother, let me have joy of thee in the ADONAY: refresh my bowels in the   
ADONAY.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD><P>     
Having confidence in thy obedience I wrote unto thee, knowing that thou wilt    
also do more than I say.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V22><H4>22</H4>
</TD><TD><P>But withal prepare me also a lodging: for I trust that through your 
prayers I shall be given unto you.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V23> 
<H4>23</H4></TD><TD><P>There salute thee Epaphras, my fellowprisoner in         
MASHIYACH YAHSHUA;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V24><H4>24</H4></TD> 
<TD><P>Marcus, Aristarchus, Demas, Lucas, my fellowlabourers.</P></TD></TR><TR> 
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V25><H4>25</H4></TD><TD><P>The grace of our ADONAY       
YAHSHUA MASHIYACH be with your spirit. Amen.</P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--This      
